Mauritius Cuts Fuel Tax, Drops Gasoline Price After Inflation Accelerates

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-03-29T08:49:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/mauritius-cuts-fuel-tax-drops-gasoline-price-after-inflation-accelerates.html
Mauritius  will temporarily reduce
taxes on fuel to allow for prices cuts and alleviate the effect
of rising international  oil prices , Finance Minister Pravind
Jugnauth said.  The price of gasoline will decline 3.9 percent to 49.3
rupees a liter and the diesel price falls 5.3 percent to 41.2
rupees a liter, Jugnauth said in a e-mailed response today to a
parliamentary question.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in  Port Louis  at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  